<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-11-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-11-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="206" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 16387/1.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Morgan</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-11-04"><hi rend="italic">November 4,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Ex-President Palma died at 11 o’clock to-night at Santiago de Cuba.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan.</hi></signed></closer>
